Revisiting Lab 2

1

ggplot(data = surveys, mapping = aes(x = weight, 
                                     y = fct_reorder(species, weight))) +
  geom_jitter(width = 0.1, height = 0.1, color = "tomato", alpha = 0.2) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.alpha = 0) +
  labs(x = "Weight of Rodent (g)", y = "Species of Rodent")

ggplot(data = surveys, mapping = aes(x = weight, 
                                     y = fct_reorder(species, weight))) +
  geom_jitter(width = 0.1, height = 0.1, color = "tomato", alpha = 0.2) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.alpha = 0) +
  labs(x = "Weight of Rodent (g)", y = "", title = "Weight of Rodent by Genus")

Time-Series Plots

1

ggplot(data = surveys, mapping = aes(x = date, y = weight, color = genus)) +
  geom_line() +
  theme_minimal()

2

mean_weights <- surveys |>
  group_by(genus, date) |>
  summarize(weight = mean(weight))

ggplot(data = mean_weights, mapping = aes(x = date, y = weight, 
                                          color = genus)) +
  geom_line() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(x = "Year", y = "", title = "Weight of Rodent by Species")

3

ggplot(data = mean_weights, mapping = aes(x = date, y = weight, 
                                          color = fct_reorder(genus, weight, 
                                                              .desc = TRUE))) +
  geom_line() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(x = "Year", y = "", title = "Weight of Rodent by Species")

4

ggplot(data = mean_weights, mapping = aes(x = date, y = weight, 
                                          color = fct_reorder(genus, weight, 
                                                              .desc = TRUE))) +
  geom_line() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(x = "Year", y = "", title = "Weight of Rodent by Species",
       color = "Rodent Genus")

Captures over the Week

1

captures <- surveys |>
  count(day_of_week) |>
  drop_na() 

ggplot(data = captures, mapping = aes(y = n, x = day_of_week)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  labs(y = "", x = "Day", 
       title = "Number of Rodents Captured by Day of Week")

2

ggplot(data = captures, mapping = aes(y = n, x = factor(day_of_week, 
                                                        levels = c("Mon", "Tue", 
                                                                   "Wed", "Thu", 
                                                                   "Fri", "Sat", 
                                                                   "Sun")))) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  labs(y = "", x = "Day", 
       title = "Number of Rodents Captured by Day of Week")

3

halfweek_captures <- surveys |>
  count(day_of_week) |>
  drop_na() |>
  mutate(
    day_of_week = fct_collapse(day_of_week, 
                               "Weekday" = c("Mon", "Tue", "Wed", "Thu", "Fri"),
                               "Weekend" = c("Sat", "Sun")
    )
  )

ggplot(data = halfweek_captures, mapping = aes(y = n, x = day_of_week)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  labs(y = "", x = "Part of Week", 
       title = "Number of Rodents Captured by Part of Week")

```{r setup}
library(tidyverse)
library(forcats)
library(here)

```

```{r data}
surveys <- read_csv(file = here("Week2", "Lab2", "surveys.csv"))
```
## Revisiting Lab 2

### 1 

```{r}
ggplot(data = surveys, mapping = aes(x = weight, 
                                     y = fct_reorder(species, weight))) +
  geom_jitter(width = 0.1, height = 0.1, color = "tomato", alpha = 0.2) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.alpha = 0) +
  labs(x = "Weight of Rodent (g)", y = "Species of Rodent")
```

### 2
```{r}
ggplot(data = surveys, mapping = aes(x = weight, 
                                     y = fct_reorder(species, weight))) +
  geom_jitter(width = 0.1, height = 0.1, color = "tomato", alpha = 0.2) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.alpha = 0) +
```

## Time-Series Plots

### 1
```{r}
ggplot(data = surveys, mapping = aes(x = date, y = weight, color = genus)) +
  geom_line() +
  theme_minimal()
```
### 2
```{r}
mean_weights <- surveys |>
  group_by(genus, date) |>
  summarize(weight = mean(weight))

ggplot(data = mean_weights, mapping = aes(x = date, y = weight, 
                                          color = genus)) +
  geom_line() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(x = "Year", y = "", title = "Weight of Rodent by Species")
```

### 3
```{r}
ggplot(data = mean_weights, mapping = aes(x = date, y = weight, 
                                          color = fct_reorder(genus, weight, 
                                                              .desc = TRUE))) +
  geom_line() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(x = "Year", y = "", title = "Weight of Rodent by Species")
```

### 4
```{r}
ggplot(data = mean_weights, mapping = aes(x = date, y = weight, 
                                          color = fct_reorder(genus, weight, 
                                                              .desc = TRUE))) +
  geom_line() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(x = "Year", y = "", title = "Weight of Rodent by Species",
       color = "Rodent Genus")
```

## Captures over the Week

### 1
```{r}
captures <- surveys |>
  count(day_of_week) |>
  drop_na() 

ggplot(data = captures, mapping = aes(y = n, x = day_of_week)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  labs(y = "", x = "Day", 
       title = "Number of Rodents Captured by Day of Week")
```

### 2
```{r}
ggplot(data = captures, mapping = aes(y = n, x = factor(day_of_week, 
                                                        levels = c("Mon", "Tue", 
                                                                   "Wed", "Thu", 
                                                                   "Fri", "Sat", 
                                                                   "Sun")))) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  labs(y = "", x = "Day", 
       title = "Number of Rodents Captured by Day of Week")
```


### 3
```{r}
halfweek_captures <- surveys |>
  count(day_of_week) |>
  drop_na() |>
  mutate(
    day_of_week = fct_collapse(day_of_week, 
                               "Weekday" = c("Mon", "Tue", "Wed", "Thu", "Fri"),
                               "Weekend" = c("Sat", "Sun")
    )
  )

ggplot(data = halfweek_captures, mapping = aes(y = n, x = day_of_week)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  labs(y = "", x = "Part of Week", 
       title = "Number of Rodents Captured by Part of Week")
```
